  "l1Title": "The planet\nhas a fever",
  "l1Body": "Imagine the Earth is your body. When you have a fever of just 1°C, you already feel terrible. The Earth is already 1.2°C warmer than 150 years ago… and it keeps rising every year.",
  "l1FactLabel": "FACT",
  "l1Fact": "2023 was the hottest year ever recorded. The 10 hottest years in history have all been in the last 10 years.",
  "l1TempLow": "Slight glacial melting",
  "l1TempNow": "Where we are today 📍",
  "l1TempHeat": "Extreme heat waves",
  "l1TempCrisis": "Civilization at risk",

  "l2Title": "The invisible\ngas",
  "l2Body": "When you burn gasoline, gas or coal — or when food decomposes — CO₂ is released. This gas acts like a blanket: it lets the sun's heat in, but doesn't let it out. The planet warms.",
  "l2FactLabel": "ANALOGY",
  "l2Fact": "It's like leaving the car running inside a closed garage. Except the garage is the entire Earth's atmosphere.",
  "l2Step1": "Sun sends\nheat",
  "l2Step2": "Earth\nreceives",
  "l2Step3": "CO₂ traps\nthe heat",
  "l2Result": "🌡️ Heat can't escape → temperature rises",

  "l3Title": "Your personal\nfootprint",
  "l3Body": "Your \"carbon footprint\" is the total CO₂ you produce in a year. It includes everything you consume: the bus you take, the burger you eat, the shirt you buy, the hot shower you take.",
  "l3FactLabel": "IN COLOMBIA",
  "l3Fact": "A Colombian produces an average of 1.8 tonnes of CO₂ per year. The world average is 4.7 t. The target to save the planet is to reach 2 t before 2030.",
  "l3ColombiaLabel": "Colombia\naverage",
  "l3WorldLabel": "World\naverage",
  "l3TargetLabel": "2030\nTarget 🎯",

  "l4Title": "Where does\nit come from?",
  "l4Body": "It's not just cars that pollute. Your footprint comes from 6 major categories of your daily life. Some are surprising: beef emits more CO₂ than driving a car.",
  "l4FactLabel": "THE 6 CATEGORIES",
  "l4Fact": "Transport and food together account for more than 55% of your total footprint.",

  "l5Title": "How much\nis too much?",
  "l5Body": "There is a global target: to avoid the worst effects of climate change, every person in the world needs to reach less than 2 tonnes of CO₂ per year by 2030.",
  "l5FactLabel": "COMPARISON",
  "l5Fact": "A US citizen produces 15 t/year. A German: 9 t. A Colombian: 1.8 t. But quality of life doesn't have to drop to reduce your footprint.",

  "l6Title": "You can\nchange something",
  "l6Body": "You don't need to be an activist or change your life overnight. Small changes in your transport, food, and home habits can reduce your footprint by up to 40%.",
  "l6FactLabel": "THE FIRST STEP",
  "l6Fact": "Knowing your footprint is the first step. What you don't measure, you can't improve. Take the test now!",
